Closing question ...

For Newcastle area
* There are many people who live in Newcastle and work in Sydney or Canberra (Professions such as IT, Legal, Consulting, etc).  They typically commute and stay in serviced appartments or the like for part of the week and WFH from the remainder.
* Conversely there are many organisations in Newcastle requiring access to emerging technical skills (not locally available) in order to expand and modernise (for example Cloud or AI skills).  Remote work options would improve the availability of high quality candidates for these roles.
* Densification will result in an increase in population, however an increase in local jobs and industry would be required to support these people.  Remote work would buffer this capability until local industry catches up, and also allow for development of Newcastle as an incubator of specialised skills.

